17 (C) issue the obligor a receipt in a form prescribed by the
18 bureau with the total amount withheld for delinquent child
19 support and the administrative fee.
20 (c) (d) The bureau shall notify the obligor at the address provided
21 by the certificate holder or vendor that the bureau intends to offset the
22 obligor's delinquent child support with the winnings.
23 (d) (e) The bureau shall hold the amount withheld from the
24 winnings of an obligor for ten (10) business days before applying the
25 amount as payment to the obligor's delinquent child support.
26 (e) (f) The delinquent child support required to be withheld under
27 this section and an administrative fee described under subsection (b)(1)
28 (c)(1) have priority over any secured or unsecured claim on winnings
29 except claims for federal or state taxes that are required to be withheld
